text:
How the Top 15 football teams fared in Week 8 
Baltimore-area high school sports photos from October 2015. Katherine Dunn Contact Reporter The Baltimore Sun How many Top 15 football teams remain undefeated after eight weeks? 
The fall season is winding down with eight weeks completed and the top high school football teams continue to separate themselves from the rest of the pack. 
Only one Top 15 team lost to an unranked team this week -- Mervo, which had gone undefeated through its first seven games. That leaves just five unbeaten teams -- Old Mill, Howard, John Carroll, Eastern Tech and Dundalk -- as the season moves quickly toward the playoffs. 
Here's a look at how The Baltimore Sun's Top 15 teams fared this weekend. Check baltimoresun.com on Monday and the paper on Tuesday for the new poll. 
Ranking/Teams/Record/This week’s result/Next opponent 
1.Gilman /8-1/Def. Friendship Collegiate Academy (D.C.) 41-0/At Calvert Hall, Friday 
2. Old Mill /8-0/Def. Broadneck 38-22/At Meade, Friday 
3. Mount Saint Joseph /7-2/Def. Calvert Hall 43-30/Vs. Loyola Blakefield, Saturday 
The Baltimore Sun takes Athletes of the Week nominations from Friday night until Sunday at 6 p.m. Please provide name, school, class, sport, position, team results and the athlete's accomplishments for the week, with statistics by game, and other supporting information. Coaches also should provide a number where they can be reached Sunday night. You can email your nominations to athleteoftheweek@baltimoresun.com . (Katherine Dunn, Glenn Graham)

12. Mervo /7-1/Lost to Edmondson 18-15/At City, Friday 
13. South Carroll /7-1/Def. North Carroll 36-6/At Century, Friday 
14. Arundel /5-3/Def. Northeast 58-6/Vs. South River, Friday 
15. Dundalk /8-0/Def. Parkville 28-0/Vs. Perry Hall, Friday
